<subSubSection id="C7CE65215F385214FF13FE57FDAA1366" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8F6B36AA5F385214FF13FE57FDAA1366" blockId="6.[177,1085,477,558]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125">
Comment: 
<taxonomicName id="48D44D295F385214FEFEFE54FDEF10BA" authorityName="RYVKIN" authorityYear="1989" box="[348,546,477,499]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tetartopeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lentus">
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F385214FEFEFE54FDEF10BA" box="[348,546,477,499]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125">Tetartopeus lentus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from the Transbaikal region; the aedeagus is illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EB454B5B5F385214FD9CFE71FD121359" author="RYVKIN A" box="[574,735,507,529]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125" pagination="66 - 77" refId="ref6553" refString="RYVKIN A. B. (1989): New species of Paederinae (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) from Siberia and Mongolia. - Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 68: 66 - 77." type="journal article" year="1989">RYVKIN (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. The previously unknown female secondary sexual characters are as follows:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C7CE65215F385214FF65FDB7FBED13C5" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125" type="description">
<paragraph id="8F6B36AA5F385214FF65FDB7FBED13C5" blockId="6.[178,1085,573,654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125">
: tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="17EF2A2F5F385214FEF4FDB7FE5E131B" box="[342,403,573,595]" captionStart="Figs 8-10" captionStartId="5.[178,218,643,665]" captionTargetBox="[190,1082,225,609]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1082,212,618]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 8-10: Tetartopeus lomnickii (ROUBAL) (8) and T. lentus RYVKIN (9-10): (8) apical portion of dorsal plate of aedeagus in dorsal view; (9) female tergite VIII; (10) female tergite IX. Scale bars: 9-10: 0.5 mm; 8: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307289/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) transverse, with almost truncate and in the middle weakly pointed posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="17EF2A2F5F385214FDA2FDD0FD8C1338" box="[512,577,602,624]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1488,1510]" captionTargetBox="[181,1074,213,1457]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[178,1082,212,1463]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Tetartopeus lomnickii (ROUBAL) (1-6) and T. lentus RYVKIN (7): (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VII; (4) male sternite VIII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (7) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3-7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307287" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307287/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) much longer than tergite VIII, posteriorly produced and broadly truncate; tergite IX (
<figureCitation id="17EF2A2F5F385214FDE0FDFDFD4113C6" box="[578,652,631,654]" captionStart="Figs 8-10" captionStartId="5.[178,218,643,665]" captionTargetBox="[190,1082,225,609]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1082,212,618]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 8-10: Tetartopeus lomnickii (ROUBAL) (8) and T. lentus RYVKIN (9-10): (8) apical portion of dorsal plate of aedeagus in dorsal view; (9) female tergite VIII; (10) female tergite IX. Scale bars: 9-10: 0.5 mm; 8: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307289/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) deeply and narrow incised posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C7CE65215F385214FF10FD17FCFC13FB" box="[178,817,669,691]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1125" type="discussion">
